✨✨ This skincare routine cleared my skin & gave me that glow everyone keeps asking about 👇

No filters, no fancy facials—just a routine that works 💆‍♀️ I struggled with dullness, texture, and dehydration until I committed to this simple yet effective glow-up lineup 💧

Here’s the routine that changed the game for me:

🫧 Anua Heartleaf Cleanser – Deep cleanses without stripping, calms irritation
🌿 Wishful Get Clean Cleanser – My go-to for removing makeup + dead skin gently
🌸 Pixi Rose Water Toner – Hydrating & preps skin like a dream
🥑 Kiehl’s Avocado Eye Cream (PM) – Revived my tired, puffy eyes overnight
💧 L’Oréal Hyaluron Eye Cream (AM) – Lightweight + perfectly hydrating for mornings
🧴 Kiehl’s Ultra Facial Cream – Locks in moisture and soothes inflammation
🚰 Laneige Water Bank Moisturizer (PM) – Extra hydration & barrier repair while I sleep
☀️ Mixsoon Centella SPF 50+ – Lightweight, non-greasy & no white cast—the dream

🔁 Now here’s the glow-boosting secret I rotate between:

✨ COSRX Retinol 0.1% Serum (2x/week PM) – Super beginner-friendly, great for refining texture + preventing early signs of aging. Start slow, always follow with moisturizer.
✨ IT Cosmetics Bye Bye Pores Glycolic Acid Serum (2x/week PM) – Gently exfoliates, reduces dark spots + smooths pores like magic!

‼️ Don’t mix retinol and glycolic acid together — I keep a 48-hour gap between them to avoid irritation.

✨ I stuck to this routine consistently for a few weeks, and not only did my skin clear up, it started glowing—smooth, hydrated, and happy.

➡️ Save this post for when you’re ready to glow up your skincare routine.
Because let’s be honest… clear skin isn’t a mystery, it’s consistency + the right products 🫶
